OL,3,CTrump raises doubts about election
OL,4,Cinterference ahead of US midterms
OL,6,FElection security experts have said
OL,7,Fthat America's decentralised voting
OL,8,Fsystem, where states are in charge of
OL,9,Findividual systems rather than the
OL,10,Ffederal government, is a strength.
OL,12,FAmericans vote in more than 10,000
OL,13,Fdifferent jurisdictions with different
OL,14,Frules, making the nations' elections
OL,15,Fcomplicated but safe from widespread
OL,16,Ffraud.
OL,18,FFrom Westminster to Washington DC -
OL,19,Four political experts are across all
OL,20,Fthe latest key talking points. Listen
OL,21,Fto the latest episode below...
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/8
